sentences: Maya Lavelle (born June 2, 1992) is an international singer-songwriter, composer, record producer and music video producer of Dutch nationality, born in Belgrade, grew up in Amsterdam, lived in Los Angeles and now residing in Curaçao.
Her first chart success came with the release of her song titled "Ben" which was featured on BBC Introducing and reached Number 1 in the iTunes Top Charts in Netherlands on 19 December 2017.

Maya Lavelle (born June 2, 1992) is an international singer-songwriter, composer, record producer and music video producer of Dutch nationality, born in Belgrade, grew up in Amsterdam, lived in Los Angeles and now residing in Curaçao.
She followed this up with the song "My Summer", for which she was executive producer and art director of the music video.
A similar theme continued with her metaphorically titled song "Zombietown" which is set in a post-apocalyptic future caused by the negligence of the human race towards climate change.
